│ The `CreateExtractElement` method in `IRBuilderBase` returns a `Value*` and not necessarily an         │
│ `ExtractElementInst*`. The `cast<ExtractElementInst>` in `translateExtract` assumes that the returned  │
│ value is always of type `ExtractElementInst`, which is incorrect and leads to the assertion failure.   │
│                                                                                                        │
│ To fix this, we need to verify the type of the returned value before casting it. If the value is not   │
│ of the expected type, we should handle it appropriately (e.g., return `nullptr` or log an error).      │
